e, England, United Kingdom","Noseley, Leicestershire, England":"Noseley, Leicestershire, England","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","Lutterworth, Leicestershire, England":"Lutterworth, Leicestershire, England","Leicester, Leicestershire, England":"Leicester, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Peabody","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: nickname ‘peacock-body’, from Middle English <i>pe</i>, <i>pey</i>, <i>pay</i> (Old English <i>pēa</i>) ‘peacock’ + <i>body</i>, perhaps for a vain person who dressed ostentatiously. Compare   Pea  ,   Peacock  .","History: The prominent financier and philanthropist George Peabody was born 1795 in South Danvers, now Peabody, MA. His first ancestor in America was Francis Peabody, who emigrated from England in 1635 and settled at Topsfield, MA."],"variants":[{"name":"Pea","meanings":["English:","nickname from Middle English <i>pa(we)</i>, <i>po(we)</i> ‘peacock’ (Old English <i>pāwa</i> and Old Norse <i>pá</i>). See   Peacock  . Alternatively, from the Middle English personal name <i>Pawe</i> (Old English <i>Pāwa</i>), Latinized as <i>Pavo</i>, and derived from the nickname.","from the Middle English personal name <i>Paw(e)</i>, a pet form of <i>Paulin</i> or occasionally <i>Paul</i>. See   Pawson  ,   Paulin  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Peabody was born in 1480, in Noseley, Leicestershire, England, his father, John Peabody, was 20 and his mother, Agnes Mosley, was 16. He married Margarett Erskine in 1499, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1544, in Leicestershire, England, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1480–1544":"1480–1544","1480–1559":"1480–1559","1500–1569":"1500–1569","1460–1520":"1460–1520","1464–1480":"1464–1480","1569":"1569","1500":"1500","1544":"1544","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","1464":"1464","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","Bef. 1480":"enne 1480","1559":"1559","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Noseley, Leicestershire, England":"Noseley, Leicestershire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lutterworth, Leicestershire, England":"Lutterworth, Leicestershire, England","Leicester, Leicestershire, England":"Leicester, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1480–1544":"1480–1544","1480–1559":"1480–1559","1500–1569":"1500–1569","1460–1520":"1460–1520","1464–1480":"1464–1480","1569":"1569","1500":"1500","1544":"1544","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","1464":"1464","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","Bef. 1480":"ennen vuotta 1480","1559":"1559","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Noseley, Leicestershire, England":"Noseley, Leicestershire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningas